The optimal treatment involves utilizing minimal-invasive techniques such as a mandibular fixation device which ensures precise alignment and protection against potential neurological complications associated with limited osseous continuity. Hence,
\boxed{\text{mandibular fixator}} is recommended given its ability to provide stable correction whilst preserving soft tissue health around sensitive areas including facial nerves. This approach balances efficacy with safety concerning long-term functional outcomes post-recovery.

